args:
A trap set by the Other has the party in a tight
spot. Though Mascula had closed off his heart,
Laxi awakens him in hopes of a resolution.
With new resolve, the pair manages to activate
a new mode called Eden, which they use to free
the group from its predicament.
Good idea. It's still a little ways to the\nthrone room, so we should rest up\nwhile we have the chance.
This place really takes me back.\nI remember how Zethia and I... Huh?
Zethia passed by just now!\nShe went into that room!
You sure about that, boss? I mean, she's\nstill possessed by the Other, yeah?
No, it was definitely her. I know it was.\nBut where did she... Ah!
Dammit! I KNEW this was a trap!
Not good. Everyone, out of the room now!
Everybody back away from the\nmiasma and... Urgh!
This is a tight spot indeed...
I'm feeling pretty wobbly over here, guys...
Th-this is my fault...\nWe have to...fight...
This miasma appears to only affect\nhumanoid life forms. I can still fight.
I am a combat android. I am a weapon.\nI protect life, bring peace, and deter war.
It cannot end here. I will not let it end.\nI wish for peace!
J-just go, Laxi... Find a way to escape...
Denied. I will fight until I break.
It is still possible for everyone to survive.\nBut to do that...I need Mascula. Rendering\ndepiction of psychological abstraction now.
I'm entering our heart...to search for\nMascula.
Target located. Mascula, everyone is\nin danger. I seek your aid.
▷I can't do it anymore.\nI can't go out there.◁
If you don't go now, there will be no peace.\nPlease help.
▷I can't. I don't want to see\nany more death or pain.◁
▷If not for me, all of our siblings\nwould still be alive.◁
▷I could be the cause of more pain and\ndeath in the future... And I can't take\nthat. I just can't!◁
I thought your heart was more advanced\nthan mine. That you were closer to being\nhuman. I envied you.
But I was mistaken. I understand our\nlost siblings' hearts better than you.
Our previous Maestro wrote in our hearts\nthat death was something painful and\nfrightening.
Our android siblings shared that concept\nof death, yet charged toward the magical\nfield emitter regardless.
Do you not understand their hearts?\nTheir powerful yearning for peace?\nYou must.
I say it again, Mascula: Help me. Please.
▷Oh, Laxi. I'm so sorry. All I ever do is let\nmyself get hurt, which means you end up\ndoing all the fighting.◁
Apologies and explanations are not\nrequired. Right now, we must prioritize\nrescuing the others.
▷Okay, but how am I supposed to help?\nEven now, I still abhor fighting.◁
You can lend me your heart.\nJoin with me now.
There's no time. Commencing operation.\nAll limiters released.
I leave the rest to you, Mascula...\nHostile targets locked.\nCommencing termination.
It's the same mode she used when\nshe went berserk that one time!
So she might ATTACK us right now?!
Right now, she seems to be concentrating\nher immense power on the fiends. But...
Ready yourselves! She comes for us!
She is refocusing her attacks on the fiends!
▷Laxi! Three fiends to your left!◁\nCommencing attack.
It's Mascula! He's guiding the assault!
So now she can actually control who\nshe goes after in her berserker state?\nNow THAT'S what I'm talkin' about!
While welcome news for us, it does not\nchange the fact she is outnumbered.
▷Annihilation mode is a double-edged\nsword, but I see no other option!◁
▷What?! Something is flowing into my\nhead... No, into my heart.◁
▷A new mode accessible from\nannihilation mode?! What is this for?!◁
▷This is our only choice. Do it, Laxi!◁\nMode change initiated.
She is absorbing all of the surrounding\nmana and giving it form, just like the\nmana kiln we found back in Lake Reeve!
▷I've never felt such power inside us!\nBut if this continues, Laxi's body will...◁

▷Laxi, you've got thirty seconds until our
core temperature reaches critical levels,
so whatever you're gonna do, do it now!◁
Initiating...enemy...destruction!
Calculating remaining enemy targets...\nCalibrating optimum route...\nOperation commencing!
▷Critical temperature levels in five...\nfour...three...\nInitiating forced shutdown of Eden mode!◁
By Ilia... She destroyed every\nlast one of the fiends.
▷Sorry if I shocked you, everyone.\nBut I'm all right now.◁
Mascula! I knew it was you! You're back!
We're all happy to have you back,\nbut what just happened? Your arms\nand legs changed...
I had an idea that if Mascula was present,\nhe could exert an artificial control over\nannihilation mode.

▷And once that worked, we discovered
there was a second mode BEYOND
annihilation mode—one we didn't
even know about.◁
Annihilation mode can't be controlled.\nThat means mode changing from\nannihilation mode should be impossible.
▷It's as if he knew our hearts would\none day become one. But how...?◁

Ya won't catch me lookin' that gift horse
in the mouth. You were always one'a our
toughest allies, and now yer even stronger!
Sounds like a win in my book.
Yeah, well, I don't care about any of that.\nAre YOU okay with this, Mascula?
You've never wanted to fight, and if you're\ncontrolling Laxi's body, isn't that the same\nas doing it yourself?
▷Heh. You're a good friend to be\nworried about me, Luca.◁

▷And you're right—I hate fighting and I
don't want to do it. So I'm going to keep
searching for a path where I have to
battle as little as possible.◁
▷But I'm not going to run anymore.\nFrom fighting...or myself.◁
I appreciate your conviction, Mascula.\nIt's very reassuring.
All right, everyone! It's time to hit that\nthrone room and take down Morsayati!
